 {"id":"bd-mblr.4.5","title":"Complete E2E script-suite coverage and execution manifest","description":"Create an authoritative map and runner strategy for every e2e integration script so the suite is complete, deterministic, and auditable. Scope: inventory all e2e/*.sh and equivalent integration entrypoints, map each to canonical scenario IDs, identify blind spots, and define one reproducible execution manifest covering required environment, ordering, and expected artifacts.","design":"Treat script-suite coverage as a data product: maintain machine-readable manifest + traceability matrix consumed by CI and triage tooling.","acceptance_criteria":"- Authoritative inventory includes every E2E script entrypoint with deterministic invocation contract and scenario coverage mapping.
- Execution manifest defines canonical ordering/sharding rules, required environment, and artifact expectations.
- Any uncovered scenario is explicitly flagged with rationale and linked remediation task.","notes":"This track complements scenario implementation by guaranteeing script-level executability and auditability of the full E2E surface.","status":"deferred","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:28:54.704231383Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T01:34:34.708187573Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4.5","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:28:54.704231383Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1364,"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4.5","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Queue-hygiene adjustment (2026-02-13): this bead is a coordination container for child implementation beads, so status is set to deferred to keep br ready/bv picks focused on executable leaf work. Scope and acceptance criteria are unchanged; completion is rolled up from children.","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:34:34Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-mblr.4.5.1","title":"E2E script inventory and scenario traceability matrix","description":"Build a complete machine-readable matrix: script path, invocation contract, scenario IDs covered, storage mode, concurrency mode, failure artifact paths, and logging schema version. Acceptance: no uncataloged e2e integration script remains; each scenario has explicit script linkage or an intentional gap annotation with rationale.","design":"Generate baseline inventory automatically, then curate explicit overrides for ambiguous mappings to minimize drift.","acceptance_criteria":"1. Matrix includes every e2e script/entrypoint with scenario IDs, invocation contract, storage/concurrency modes, deterministic seed source, required artifacts, and log schema version. 2. Every canonical P0/P1 scenario is mapped to at least one script or linked to an explicit gap issue. 3. Output is machine-readable and diff-friendly for CI drift checks.","notes":"Primary traceability key is scenario_id; this matrix must stay aligned with bd-mblr.4.1.2.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:29:00.232621941Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T00:46:56.821594373Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4.5.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.1.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:29:00.232621941Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4.5.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:29:00.232621941Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4.5.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.5","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:29:00.232621941Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-mblr.4.5.2","title":"Deterministic full-suite e2e script orchestrator and manifest","description":"Define and implement a single orchestrated execution manifest for all required e2e scripts (ordering, shardability, retries policy, timeout budgets, and required artifacts). Acceptance: one command executes the canonical full e2e script suite and emits a deterministic summary (pass/fail + missing scenarios + artifact index).","design":"Implement manifest-driven orchestrator with explicit phase boundaries and stable run identifiers for correlation.","acceptance_criteria":"1. One canonical command runs the full required e2e script suite with deterministic ordering and declared shard strategy. 2. Run summary reports per-script status, covered/missing scenarios, and artifact index. 3. Runner exits non-zero for missing required scenarios, missing artifacts, or nondeterministic manifest violations.","notes":"Orchestrator/manifest is implemented before final script-gap closure so missing lanes are surfaced early and consumed by downstream implementation + CI gates. It defines the canonical deterministic execution contract that all script additions must register against.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:29:05.671041538Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T01:33:50.157893958Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4.5.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.3.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:46:40.083981564Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4.5.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.5","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:29:05.671041538Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4.5.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.5.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:29:05.671041538Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1352,"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4.5.2","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Dependency rationale: bd-mblr.4.3.1 is now a prerequisite so the full-suite orchestrator cannot claim deterministic execution without an explicit seed manifest/CLI contract.","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:47:07Z"}]}
-{"id":"bd-mblr.4.5.3","title":"Implement missing e2e integration scripts for uncovered critical scenarios","description":"Close uncovered critical-scenario gaps discovered by the matrix, especially concurrency conflict windows, crash/recovery boundaries, and compatibility roundtrips. Acceptance: every P0/P1 scenario in the canonical catalog has at least one deterministic e2e script path with reproducible evidence artifacts.","design":"Prioritize high-risk scenario families first (concurrency conflict windows, crash/recovery boundaries, compatibility roundtrips).","acceptance_criteria":"1. All uncovered canonical P0/P1 scenarios (transaction/recovery, concurrency/corruption, compatibility roundtrips) gain deterministic script coverage. 2. New scripts run against real file-backed paths where applicable and are registered in traceability + orchestrator manifests. 3. Each script emits reproducible failure artifacts sufficient for offline replay and diagnosis.","notes":"Missing-script implementation now depends on inventory, logging profile, and the canonical orchestrator contract; every new script must register into orchestrator + traceability manifests and emit reproducible artifact/log outputs.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:29:11.477120256Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T01:33:50.445202166Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.2.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:29:11.477120256Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.2.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:29:11.477120256Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.2.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:29:11.477120256Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4